data.description:
This is a very unique home with a massive year round
creek up to 50 feet wide. With swimming holes, water 
falls and springs, all on the property of 10.5 acres of forest
surrounding the Glen . It is secluded in  its own valley, 
with Sacramento Mountain as your backyard.  It is 
 the highest mountain in the area. Shasta lake is within 10 minutes away. Mt Shasta is 30 minutes away.

You are 5 minutes from I5 but you cannot hear it. The 
House was rebuilt completely in 1996. Down to 2x4’s
and roof rafters. It has many patios, decks and lot’s of landscaping around the property. It is 2 very large 
Bedrooms one large bath with sunken tub and a ¼ bath  that could be easily turned into a  ½ bath. Dinning , living room and den. Rinnia heater or fireplace. There is another 400sq ft building that is finished.Has water and wood stove could be mother inlaw, tenant, teenagers, or a study. A very unique place with a lot of Nature, Peace and Quiet. Unfortunately last July; a year ago, the Salt fire came through. It destroyed a lot of forest and other things which were replaced and whole again.Water system is new. Even with the loss it is still special and the forest has rebounded with thunder, and filled in beautifully. She is now more meadow looking which is still rare.
The home itself has been nurtured and turned into a beautiful mountain oasis. From the wood doors to beautiful crown molding, Gorgeous hand done pine panel throughout home as well as inset huge bay windows with seating looking out to the creek. The gardens have been loved and nourished by a green thumb , with gorgeous flowers, vegetables, strawberry patches, and fruit trees. 
The home boasts many pluses, from the sunken garden tub to the shower with steam. There is a large laundry room inside with storage and a wash sink. As well as an outside sink along the shop with counter spaces. garden windows in kitchen.
The creek is only a couple of miles long comes from a spring
And is the purest water you will ever drink. And it tastes good.
There are only 4 houses on the creek , 2 which are at the other end of the creek. A lot of critters from bald eagles to otters,hummingbirds and a lot of other birds. A Must See!
data.whatILove:
the massive creek flows thru property year round. gardens quiet peaceful
yet 5 mins from i-5  but no noise, except wild life. another building finished
for anything you want it to be. 400sq.ft.
